          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "AnomalyUsageDeviation",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to calculate deviations in energy and demand usage for accounts between two billing periods. It compares the most recent billing period with the previous one, calculating percentage deviations in energy and demand usage for each account. The results are filtered to include only those deviations that meet or exceed specified minimum thresholds."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple steps, including data retrieval, calculation of deviations, and filtering based on conditions. It uses nested queries and joins, which adds to its complexity. However, it does not involve complex logic or multiple layers of nested operations, keeping it at a medium complexity level."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
